FBIS3-23564 "jpuma010___94007" JPRS-UMA-94-010 Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Central Eurasia Military Affairs 18 February 1994 CIS/RUSSIAN MILITARY ISSUES POLICY Varennikov Calls Indictment `Fantasy' 94UM0249B Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 18 Feb 94 p 1 94UM0249B Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA Language: Russian Article Type:CSO [Item by Petr Karapetyan, KRASNAYA ZVEZDA] [Text] On 17 February former Commander-in-Chief of Ground Troops Valentin Varennikov testified in proceedings in the case of the GKChP [State Committee for the State of Emergency]. Calling the procuracy's charges against him in the plot against President Mikhail Gorbachev a fantasy, he declared that, being in Kiev on 18 August 1991, he did not present the leadership of Ukraine with demands for supporting the GKChP and instituting a state of emergency in western oblasts of the republic, nor did he assign any missions of any kind to the Commander-in-Chief, Black Sea Fleet regarding Belbek Airfield. Varennikov emphasized that "none of this was within my competence; I did not demand, I recommended."
